## Authentication Pattern

### API Token for Server-to-Server Calls

The dashboard has NextAuth session-based auth for users. For **internal system calls**, use a separate API token.

**Environment setup:**

```bash
# In trading/.env
DASHBOARD_URL=https://winzinvest.com
DASHBOARD_API_TOKEN=randomly_generated_secret_token_here

# In trading-dashboard-public/.env.production
INTERNAL_API_TOKEN=same_token_as_above
```

**API route validation:**

```typescript
// app/api/activation/route.ts

export async function POST(req: Request) {
  const authHeader = req.headers.get('Authorization');
  
  // Check for Bearer token (server-to-server)
  if (authHeader?.startsWith('Bearer ')) {
    const token = authHeader.replace('Bearer ', '');
    if (token === process.env.INTERNAL_API_TOKEN) {
      // Valid internal call - proceed
      // ...
      return NextResponse.json({ ok: true });
    }
  }
  
  // Fallback: check NextAuth session (user-initiated call)
  const session = await getServerSession(authOptions);
  if (!session?.user?.email) {
    return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Unauthorized' }, { status: 401 });
  }
  
  // Valid user call - proceed
  // ...
}
```

**Why this pattern:**
- Supports **both** internal (trading system) and user-initiated calls
- API token for automation (stateless, no session cookies)
- Session auth for users (secure, browser-based)
- Token stored in env vars (never hardcoded)

