## State Sync Architecture

### What Syncs, What Doesn't

| Data | Source of Truth | Sync Direction | Frequency |
|---|---|---|---|
| Positions | Trading system (IBKR) | Trading → Dashboard | Every 5 min (snapshot) |
| User activation | Dashboard (tracks first trade) | Trading → Dashboard | On first fill |
| PMF survey | Dashboard | N/A (dashboard-only) | On submission |
| Kill switch state | Dashboard | Dashboard → Trading | Real-time (polling) |
| Account balance | IBKR | Trading → Dashboard | Every 5 min |
| Trade logs | Trading system | Trading → Dashboard | After every fill |

**Key insight:**
- IBKR is always the source of truth for **financial data** (positions, balance)
- Dashboard is source of truth for **user preferences and surveys**
- Trading system **writes** metrics, **reads** preferences

