## Testing Integration

### Mock the External System

When testing dashboard features that call trading system (or vice versa):

```typescript
// __tests__/activation.test.ts

// Mock fetch for external API calls
global.fetch = jest.fn().mockResolvedValue({
  ok: true,
  json: async () => ({ ok: true }),
});

// Test the feature
await recordActivation('test@example.com');
expect(fetch).toHaveBeenCalledWith(
  expect.stringContaining('/api/activation'),
  expect.objectContaining({ method: 'POST' })
);
```

**Don't test integration in production.** Use mocks or a dedicated staging environment where both systems run in test mode.

---

## Summary

| Direction | Use Case | Pattern | Critical? |
|---|---|---|---|
| Trading → Dashboard | Activation, metrics | POST with token, timeout 5s | No (warn on fail) |
| Dashboard → Trading | Kill switch, preferences | File poll or webhook | Yes (retry + alert) |
| Dashboard ← User | Surveys, settings | NextAuth session | Yes (fail if auth fails) |

**Golden rule:** Dashboard availability should never block trading execution.
